{
  "stem": "1061.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Having gotten out of those marshes, you can imagine what stroke of luck this was to find ourselves under a roof, not standing in water, not being beaten on the marches.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because the march itself, going from the Auschwitz barrack to that-- to the marshes, that also took its toll because people were being shot on the way and coming back.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we didn't have to march to the work-- to the job, because the job was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We slept indoors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We worked indoors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think this is really, in the final analysis, this phase would have finished us off-- although a lot of women from our hometown did survive.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because after-- you see, we were in that [GERMAN] unit until they were liquidating Auschwitz, which was about two months.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a lot of women who did not go with us and did join us on that death march later survived-- as I am here to attest, because I see some of them once a year when we meet for the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, everybody knows what happened when the death march occurred.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, Auschwitz was evacuated on the 18th-- officially on the 18th of January 1945.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whether we were actually on the death march on the 19th or 17th or 16th or 18th, I could not tell you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I would place it as the first half of January 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were told to just line up again and with-- got into a larger unit of women.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I went always with women, you know-- never, never with men.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we-- this is January.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's bitter winter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Snow is falling.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We're lining up to go we don't know where.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
